review_res.text: My approach was to find the smallest apple first. In doing so, this would align apples in a certain vague weight order. Once the smallest apple was done, I continued to compare apples that did not have a definite order in the line. This allowed me to organize from smallest to largest pretty quickly. Given that the fruit weights were random, sometimes I had to make more weight comparisons.

review_res.text: My approach remained the same, I sought out the smallest apple first. By searching for the lowest apple, it provided me a certain estimated weight order of the rest of the apples (because I knew they were either higher or lower weight than certain other apples). The apples that had an undefined weight were then compared against others to determine their final order. The comparisons had to go up a bit with such a high number of apples.
